    public class InRange<T extends Comparable<T>>
extends KoryphePredicate<T>

    An InRange is a Predicate that tests if a Comparable is within a provided range [start, end]. By default the range is inclusive, you can toggle this using the startInclusive and endInclusive booleans.

    If the start is not set then this will be treated as unbounded. Similarly with the end.

    If the test value is null then the predicate will return false.

    This range predicate takes a single value to test, if you want to test a startValue and endValue lies within a range then you can use the InRangeDual predicate.
